Content:
@jorian my blog post was an update as it was for 20k tx/s at the time and how we were working towards building on AWS's scalable infrastructure, the only reason to use AWS is because it's easy to provision enough resources for our scale testing.

thus far, a 64 chain cluster has been used to optimise as much as possible and debug on a smaller scale of 45k (tx or payments?) /second.

when the docker/kubernetes part has been done.  we may look at repeating tests  on non-AWS infrastructure - but this would require finding a provider with 300-500 servers available at the same scale.  We could use a smaller farm of servers - linkedin has been good for finding organisations looking at (software) scaling solutions because they have the hardware.
